		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Most of the sequence tagging tasks in natural language processing require to recognize segments with certain syntactic role or semantic meaning in a sentence . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "They are usually tackled with Conditional Random Fields ( CRFs ) , ",
			"relation": "bg-compare"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "which do indirect word-level modeling over word-level features ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "and thus cannot make full use of segment-level information . <S>",
			"relation": "progression"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Semi-Markov Conditional Random Fields ( Semi-CRFs ) model segments directly ",
			"relation": "contrast"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "but extracting segment-level features for Semi-CRFs is still a very challenging problem . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "This paper presents Gated Recursive Semi-CRFs ( grSemi-CRFs ) , ",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "which model segments directly ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "and automatically learn segment level features through a gated recursive convolutional neural network . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "Our experiments on text chunking and named entity recognition ( NER ) demonstrate ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
